1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:02,283
You have more good ideas than you will ever ship.

2
00:00:02,233 --> 00:00:04,225
A research dive you keep postponing.

3
00:00:04,225 --> 00:00:06,300
A tool you would build if you had a free week.

4
00:00:06,300 --> 00:00:10,108
A paper, a prototype, a plan — all stuck in the same place: your head.

5
00:00:10,108 --> 00:00:16,383
Not because the idea is weak — but because doing it means becoming a researcher, a critic, an engineer, and a project manager, all at once.

6
00:00:16,383 --> 00:00:17,883
So the idea waits.

7
00:00:17,883 --> 00:00:19,733
And most of them quietly die there.

